# Credit Risk Model with IV-Based Selection

This script builds a credit risk scorecard using logistic regression, with variable selection based on Information Value (IV).

## Approach

* Apply WOE (Weight of Evidence) transformation to all variables
* Compute Information Value (IV) to measure predictive strength
* Select variables with IV > 0.02
* Train a logistic regression model on selected features
* Evaluate performance using ROC and KS
* Generate credit scores using a scorecard

## Output

* ROC curve for model performance
* KS statistic for separation power
* Credit score distribution

## Notes

Using IV helps remove weak variables and results in a more stable and interpretable model compared to using all features.
